Skincare, especially sunscreen, can be expensive here, so I’m really grateful for this giveaway, Evelyn! Living in the Philippines, where the heat and humidity can be brutal (as I’m sure you’ve experienced), I’ve always struggled with products that either clog my pores or feel too heavy. Centella’s sunscreen is perfect for my busy days (which is almost every day for me) as it offers light, reliable protection without that dreaded sticky feeling. Whether I’m working in the field or just commuting, it feels breathable and keeps my skin safe without clogging my pores.

Then there’s the moisturizer, which has become my favorite part of my evening routine. After a long, hectic day, applying it feels like a small act of kindness toward myself. It’s not just skincare but self-care for me, a moment to unwind and remind myself to slow down in this very fast-paced life.

What really sets Centella apart from other brands, though, is their commitment to natural ingredients and ethical practices. Knowing their products are cruelty-free, made with sustainable ingredients, and focused on clean beauty gives me peace of mind. I’m not just taking care of my skin but supporting a brand that values the planet and animals, just as much as I do.
